7564  a transmission attempt during retries after a collision: 0 =< r <2^k */

7630  Eight sequential Reads from this address (offset 0x28) will read all Wake-UpFrame Filter Registers. */
7631 /* Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg0 : Filter 0 Byte Mask
7632  Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg1 : Filter 1 Byte Mask
7633  Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg2 : Filter 2 Byte Mask
7634  Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg3 : Filter 3 Byte Mask
7635  Wake-UpFrame Filter Reg4 : RSVD - Filter3 Command - RSVD - Filter2 Command -
7636  RSVD - Filter1 Command - RSVD - Filter0 Command
7637  Wake-UpFrame Filter Re5 : Filter3 Offset - Filter2 Offset - Filter1 Offset - Filter0 Offset
7638  Wake-UpFrame Filter Re6 : Filter1 CRC16 - Filter0 CRC16
7639  Wake-UpFrame Filter Re7 : Filter3 CRC16 - Filter2 CRC16 */

9011 /******************************************************************************/
9012 /* For a painless codes migration between the STM32F4xx device product */
9013 /* lines, the aliases defined below are put in place to overcome the */
9014 /* differences in the interrupt handlers and IRQn definitions. */
9015 /* No need to update developed interrupt code when moving across */
9016 /* product lines within the same STM32F4 Family */
9017 /******************************************************************************/
